*[[Wegener's granulomatosis]] 50-60% have ophthalmologic manifestations, which can be a presenting feature in a minority of patients. Orbital disease is the most common manifestation, and may result in [[proptosis]], [[restrictive ophthalmopathy]], chronic orbital pain, and in chronic cases, orbital retraction syndrome and intractable socket pain. Wegener's may also cause [[optic neuritis|injury to the optic nerve]], [[ophthalmoplegia]], [[conjunctivitis]], [[keratitis]], [[scleritis]], [[episcleritis]], [[dacrocystitis]], nasolacrimnal duct obstruction, [[dacroadenitis]], [[uveitis]], and retinal vasculitis.

